name: Computer
definition: A machine for performing calculations automatically.

name: Server
definition: A computer which provides some service for other computers connected to it via a network.

name: Computer Disk
definition: A flat rotating disk designed for data storage. Data is stored on either or both surfaces of disks in concentric rings called tracks.

name: CD-ROM
definition: An optical disc storage system for computers on which data can be read or from which data can be retrieved but not entered or modified.

name: Compact Disc-Interactive
definition: An optical disk that is physically the same as an audio CD, but contains multimedia information (images, sound, etc.) The user can interact with films, games and educational programs.

name: Computer Hard Disk
definition: A rigid magnetic disk mounted permanently in a drive unit.

name: Archive
definition: A place or collection containing records, documents, or other materials, especially those of historical interest.

name: Database
definition: An information set with a regular structure. Although it can be applied to any set of information the term was invented to refer to computerized data, and is used almost exclusively in computing.

name: Digital Data Repository
definition: A storage location for digital data.

name: Data Warehouse
definition: A central repository of information in a predefined and fixed schema for the purpose of analyzing the data.

name: Digital Archive
definition: A storage location for historical digital data.

name: Electronic Document Room
definition: The online repository for electronic FDA CDER submissions; it is an extension of the Central Document Room.

name: Study Data Repository
definition: A database in which study data are stored for access and use by the scientific community.

name: Storage Unit
definition: A physical structure or device capable of holding objects or samples.

name: Repository
definition: A facility where items can be deposited for storage or safekeeping.

name: Research Repository
definition: A collection of participant data and/or samples that are stored for future research.
